item.title: Niall McGuirk: Hope Collective
item.description: In this episode we talk to Niall McGuirk about the Hope Collective. Hope Collective originated in the early 1980s when Niall started putting on gigs to encourage bands to play in Dublin and developed into the Hope Collective in 1994. Hope facilitated dozens of bands playing gigs in Ireland and latterly has produced books recording the history and recollections of that music scene... Feed: https://podcast.leftarchive.ie/@ILAPodcast/feed.xml

item.title: Morning Madness & Tough Transitions: 12 Creative Ideas #444
item.description: Do you have kids that are tough to get to bed and then get out of bed the next morning?! What about kids who struggle with transitions or who are late? This podcast is packed with ideas to help you get your kids moving--without the battles--even if they struggle with ADHD or anxiety. Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/CELBL1853551588
